events.description: Following the death of Edward the Confessor on the previous day, the Witan meets to confirm Harold Godwinson as the new King of England; Harold is crowned the same day, sparking a succession crisis that will eventually lead to the Norman conquest of England.
events.html: • 1066 – Following the death of Edward the Confessor on the previous day, the Witan meets to confirm Harold Godwinson as the new King of England; Harold is crowned the same day, sparking a succession crisis that will eventually lead to the Norman conquest of England.[1]

events.description: Philip of Swabia undergoes a second coronation as King of the Romans.
events.html: • 1205 – Philip of Swabia undergoes a second coronation as King of the Romans.[2]

events.description: Stephen Uroš III is crowned King of Serbia, having defeated his half-brother Stefan Konstantin in battle. His son is crowned "young king" in the same ceremony.
events.html: • 1322 – Stephen Uroš III is crowned King of Serbia, having defeated his half-brother Stefan Konstantin in battle. His son is crowned "young king" in the same ceremony.[3]

events.description: Charles IV of Bohemia is crowned with the Iron Crown of Lombardy as King of Italy in Milan.
events.html: • 1355 – Charles IV of Bohemia is crowned with the Iron Crown of Lombardy as King of Italy in Milan.[4]

events.description: Constantine XI is crowned Byzantine Emperor at Mystras.
events.html: • 1449 – Constantine XI is crowned Byzantine Emperor at Mystras.[5]

events.description: The Catholic Monarchs Ferdinand and Isabella enter Granada at the conclusion of the Granada War.
events.html: • 1492 – The Catholic Monarchs Ferdinand and Isabella enter Granada at the conclusion of the Granada War.[6]

events.description: The first European school of higher learning in the Americas, Colegio de Santa Cruz de Tlatelolco, is founded by Viceroy Antonio de Mendoza and Bishop Juan de Zumárraga in Mexico City.
events.html: • 1536 – The first European school of higher learning in the Americas, Colegio de Santa Cruz de Tlatelolco, is founded by Viceroy Antonio de Mendoza and Bishop Juan de Zumárraga in Mexico City.[7]

entities.name: Colegio de Santa Cruz de Tlatelolco

events.description: King Henry VIII of England marries Anne of Cleves.
events.html: • 1540 – King Henry VIII of England marries Anne of Cleves.[8]

events.description: The Union of Arras unites the southern Netherlands under the Duke of Parma (Ottavio Farnese), governor in the name of King Philip II of Spain.
events.html: • 1579 – The Union of Arras unites the southern Netherlands under the Duke of Parma (Ottavio Farnese), governor in the name of King Philip II of Spain.[9]

events.description: Arauco War: The first Parliament of Quillín is celebrated, putting a temporary hold on hostilities between Mapuches and Spanish in Chile.
events.html: • 1641 – Arauco War: The first Parliament of Quillín is celebrated, putting a temporary hold on hostilities between Mapuches and Spanish in Chile.[10]

events.description: English Restoration: The Fifth Monarchists unsuccessfully attempt to seize control of London, England. The revolt is suppressed after a few days.
events.html: • 1661 – English Restoration: The Fifth Monarchists unsuccessfully attempt to seize control of London, England. The revolt is suppressed after a few days.[11]

events.description: The Committee of Inquiry on the South Sea Bubble publishes its findings, revealing details of fraud among company directors and corrupt politicians.
events.html: • 1721 – The Committee of Inquiry on the South Sea Bubble publishes its findings, revealing details of fraud among company directors and corrupt politicians.[12]

events.description: Sie werden aus Saba alle kommen, BWV 65, a Bach cantata, for Epiphany, is performed the first time.
events.html: • 1724 – Sie werden aus Saba alle kommen, BWV 65, a Bach cantata, for Epiphany, is performed the first time.[13]

entities.name: Sie werden aus Saba alle kommen, BWV 65

events.description: In the Battle of Jersey, the British defeat the last attempt by France to invade Jersey in the Channel Islands.
events.html: • 1781 – In the Battle of Jersey, the British defeat the last attempt by France to invade Jersey in the Channel Islands.[14]

events.description: Combined British, Portuguese and colonial Brazilian forces begin the Invasion of Cayenne during the Napoleonic Wars.
events.html: • 1809 – Combined British, Portuguese and colonial Brazilian forces begin the Invasion of Cayenne during the Napoleonic Wars.[15]

events.description: Alfred Vail and colleagues demonstrate a telegraph system using dots and dashes (this is the forerunner of Morse code).
events.html: • 1838 – Alfred Vail and colleagues demonstrate a telegraph system using dots and dashes (this is the forerunner of Morse code).[16]

events.description: The Night of the Big Wind, the most damaging storm in 300 years, sweeps across Ireland, damaging or destroying more than 20% of the houses in Dublin.
events.html: • 1839 – The Night of the Big Wind, the most damaging storm in 300 years, sweeps across Ireland, damaging or destroying more than 20% of the houses in Dublin.[17]

events.description: Samuel Colt obtains his first contract for the sale of revolver pistols to the United States government.
events.html: • 1847 – Samuel Colt obtains his first contract for the sale of revolver pistols to the United States government.[18]

events.description: The inauguration of the Musikverein in Vienna, Austria.
events.html: • 1870 – The inauguration of the Musikverein in Vienna, Austria.[19]

events.description: The Washington National Cathedral is chartered by Congress. The charter is signed by President Benjamin Harrison.
events.html: • 1893 – The Washington National Cathedral is chartered by Congress.[20] The charter is signed by President Benjamin Harrison.

events.description: Second Boer War: Having already besieged the fortress at Ladysmith, Boer forces attack it, but are driven back by British defenders.
events.html: • 1900 – Second Boer War: Having already besieged the fortress at Ladysmith, Boer forces attack it, but are driven back by British defenders.[21]

entities.name: United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland

events.description: Maria Montessori opens her first school and daycare center for working class children in Rome, Italy.
events.html: • 1907 – Maria Montessori opens her first school and daycare center for working class children in Rome, Italy.[22]

events.description: New Mexico is admitted to the Union as the 47th U.S. state.
events.html: • 1912 – New Mexico is admitted to the Union as the 47th U.S. state.[23]

events.description: German geophysicist Alfred Wegener first presents his theory of continental drift.
events.html: • 1912 – German geophysicist Alfred Wegener first presents his theory of continental drift.[24]

events.description: King Alexander of the Serbs, Croats and Slovenes suspends his country's constitution (the January 6th Dictatorship).
events.html: • 1929 – King Alexander of the Serbs, Croats and Slovenes suspends his country's constitution (the January 6th Dictatorship).[25]

events.description: Mother Teresa arrives by sea in Calcutta, India, to begin her work among India's poorest and sick people.
events.html: • 1929 – Mother Teresa arrives by sea in Calcutta, India, to begin her work among India's poorest and sick people.[26]

events.description: Clessie Cummins arrives at the National Automobile Show in New York City, having driven a car powered by one of his diesel engines from Indianapolis.
events.html: • 1930 – Clessie Cummins arrives at the National Automobile Show in New York City, having driven a car powered by one of his diesel engines from Indianapolis.[27]

events.description: United States President Franklin D. Roosevelt delivers his Four Freedoms speech in the State of the Union address.
events.html: • 1941 – United States President Franklin D. Roosevelt delivers his Four Freedoms speech in the State of the Union address.[28]

events.description: The first general election ever in Vietnam is held.
events.html: • 1946 – The first general election ever in Vietnam is held.[29]

events.description: Pan American Airlines becomes the first commercial airline to offer a round-the-world ticket.
events.html: • 1947 – Pan American Airlines becomes the first commercial airline to offer a round-the-world ticket.[30]

events.description: The United Kingdom recognizes the People's Republic of China. The Republic of China severs diplomatic relations with the UK in response.
events.html: • 1950 – The United Kingdom recognizes the People's Republic of China.[31] The Republic of China severs diplomatic relations with the UK in response.

events.description: Korean War: Beginning of the Ganghwa massacre, in the course of which an estimated 200–1,300 South Korean communist sympathizers are slaughtered.
events.html: • 1951 – Korean War: Beginning of the Ganghwa massacre, in the course of which an estimated 200–1,300 South Korean communist sympathizers are slaughtered.[32]

events.description: National Airlines Flight 2511 is destroyed in mid-air by a bomb, while en route from New York City to Miami.
events.html: • 1960 – National Airlines Flight 2511 is destroyed in mid-air by a bomb, while en route from New York City to Miami.[33]

events.description: The Associations Law comes into force in Iraq, allowing registration of political parties.
events.html: • 1960 – The Associations Law comes into force in Iraq, allowing registration of political parties.[34]

events.description: Vietnam War: United States Marine Corps and ARVN troops launch "Operation Deckhouse Five" in the Mekong River delta.
events.html: • 1967 – Vietnam War: United States Marine Corps and ARVN troops launch "Operation Deckhouse Five" in the Mekong River delta.[35]

entities.name: Army of the Republic of Vietnam

events.description: Allegheny Airlines Flight 737 crashes in Lafayette Township, McKean County, Pennsylvania, United States, killing 11.
events.html: • 1969 – Allegheny Airlines Flight 737 crashes in Lafayette Township, McKean County, Pennsylvania, United States, killing 11.[36]

events.description: In response to the 1973 oil crisis, daylight saving time commences nearly four months early in the United States.
events.html: • 1974 – In response to the 1973 oil crisis, daylight saving time commences nearly four months early in the United States.[37]

events.description: Satwant Singh and Kehar Singh are sentenced to death for conspiracy in the assassination of Prime Minister Indira Gandhi; the two men are executed the same day.
events.html: • 1989 – Satwant Singh and Kehar Singh are sentenced to death for conspiracy in the assassination of Prime Minister Indira Gandhi; the two men are executed the same day.[38]

events.description: President of Georgia Zviad Gamsakhurdia flees the country as a result of the military coup.
events.html: • 1992 – President of Georgia Zviad Gamsakhurdia flees the country as a result of the military coup.[39]

events.description: Indian Border Security Force units kill 55 Kashmiri civilians in Sopore, Jammu and Kashmir, in revenge after militants ambushed a BSF patrol.
events.html: • 1993 – Indian Border Security Force units kill 55 Kashmiri civilians in Sopore, Jammu and Kashmir, in revenge after militants ambushed a BSF patrol.[40]

events.description: Four people are killed when Lufthansa CityLine Flight 5634 crashes on approach to Charles de Gaulle Airport in Roissy-en-France, France.
events.html: • 1993 – Four people are killed when Lufthansa CityLine Flight 5634 crashes on approach to Charles de Gaulle Airport in Roissy-en-France, France.[41]

events.description: U.S. figure skater Nancy Kerrigan is attacked and injured by an assailant hired by her rival Tonya Harding's ex-husband during the U.S. Figure Skating Championships.
events.html: • 1994 – U.S. figure skater Nancy Kerrigan is attacked and injured by an assailant hired by her rival Tonya Harding's ex-husband during the U.S. Figure Skating Championships.[42]

events.description: A chemical fire in an apartment complex in Manila, Philippines, leads to the discovery of plans for Project Bojinka, a mass-terrorist attack.
events.html: • 1995 – A chemical fire in an apartment complex in Manila, Philippines, leads to the discovery of plans for Project Bojinka, a mass-terrorist attack.[43]

events.description: The last natural Pyrenean ibex, Celia, is killed by a falling tree, thus making the species extinct.
events.html: • 2000 – The last natural Pyrenean ibex, Celia, is killed by a falling tree, thus making the species extinct.[44]

events.description: Edgar Ray Killen is indicted for the 1964 murders of Chaney, Goodman, and Schwerner during the American Civil Rights Movement.
events.html: • 2005 – Edgar Ray Killen is indicted for the 1964 murders of Chaney, Goodman, and Schwerner during the American Civil Rights Movement.[45]

entities.name: Murders of Chaney, Goodman, and Schwerner

events.description: A train collision in Graniteville, South Carolina, United States, releases about 60 tons of chlorine gas.
events.html: • 2005 – A train collision in Graniteville, South Carolina, United States, releases about 60 tons of chlorine gas.[46]

events.description: Twenty-six people are killed and 63 wounded when a suicide bomber blows himself up at a police station in Damascus.
events.html: • 2012 – Twenty-six people are killed and 63 wounded when a suicide bomber blows himself up at a police station in Damascus.[47]

events.description: Five people are killed and six others injured in a mass shooting at Fort Lauderdale–Hollywood International Airport in Broward County, Florida.
events.html: • 2017 – Five people are killed and six others injured in a mass shooting at Fort Lauderdale–Hollywood International Airport in Broward County, Florida.[48]

events.description: Forty people are killed in a gold mine collapse in Badakhshan province, in northern Afghanistan.
events.html: • 2019 – Forty people are killed in a gold mine collapse in Badakhshan province, in northern Afghanistan.[49]

events.description: Muhammad V of Kelantan resigns as the Yang di-Pertuan Agong of Malaysia, becoming the first monarch to do so.
events.html: • 2019 – Muhammad V of Kelantan resigns as the Yang di-Pertuan Agong of Malaysia, becoming the first monarch to do so.[50]

events.description: Supporters of U.S. President Donald Trump attack the United States Capitol to disrupt certification of the 2020 presidential election, resulting in five deaths and evacuation of the U.S. Congress.
events.html: • 2021 – Supporters of U.S. President Donald Trump attack the United States Capitol to disrupt certification of the 2020 presidential election, resulting in five deaths and evacuation of the U.S. Congress.[51]

entities.name: Attempts to overturn the 2020 United States presidential election
